": "Intangible drilling and development costs\n\t\t\t\tin the case of oil and gas wells and geothermal wells", "@display-inline": "yes-display-inline"}, "paragraph": [{"#tail": "\n              ", "text": {"#tail": "\n              ", "{http://namespaces.cato.org/catoxml}entity-ref": [{"#tail": ", and except as provided in", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "subsection (a)", "@value": "Internal Revenue Code of 1986/s:263/ss:a"}, {"#tail": ", regulations shall be\n\t\t\t\tprescribed by the", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "subsection (i)", "@value": "Internal Revenue Code of 1986/s:263/ss:i"}, {"#tail": "under this subtitle corresponding to the\n\t\t\t\tregulations which granted the option to deduct as expenses intangible drilling\n\t\t\t\tand development costs in the case of oil and gas wells and which were\n\t\t\t\trecognized and approved by the", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Secretary", "@entity-id": "2000"}, {"#tail": "in", "@entity-type": "federal-body", "#text": "Congress", "@entity-id": "0001"}, {"#tail": ". Such regulations shall also grant the option to deduct\n\t\t\t\tas expenses intangible drilling and development costs in the case of wells\n\t\t\t\tdrilled for any geothermal deposit (as defined in", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "House Concurrent Resolution 50,\n\t\t\t\tSeventy-ninth Congress", "@value": "79 HConRes 50"}, {"#tail": ") to the\n\t\t\t\tsame extent and in the same manner as such expenses are deductible in the case\n\t\t\t\tof oil and gas wells. This subsection shall not apply with respect to any costs\n\t\t\t\tto which any deduction is allowed under", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "section 613(e)(2)", "@value": "Internal Revenue Code of 1986/s:613/ss:e/p:2"}, {"#tail": "or", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "section 59(e)", "@value": "Internal Revenue Code of 1986/s:59/ss:e"}, {"#tail": ".", "@entity-type": "act", "#text": "291", "@value": "Internal Revenue Code of 1986/s:291"}], "#text": "Notwithstanding", "@display-inline":